# seeds/
#
# Why this folder exists:
# Seeds populate the database with initial or test data.
# Unlike migrations, seeds are not versioned — they can be re-run.
# Useful for loading roles, permission definitions, or demo data during dev.
#
# Run all seeds:
#   npm run seed
#
# Generate a new seed:
#   knex seed:make 01_roles --knexfile src/config/knexfile.js
